:Namespace FString   
РЇЮ  Requires Dyalog 20 or later!
:Section CORE  
РЇЮ Env for РѕєF code. Remember, user code is executed in CALLER space (РіЃРјЋRSI) 
  РјЋIO РјЋML РјЋPPРєљ 0 1 34     
РЇЮ Loader РѕєF.dyalog shares transient namespace РјЋSE.РѕєFРЇЎShare, containing: 
РЇЮ - global variables in globals
РЇЮ - source for the library (┬Б,`L) code as libsrc
РЇЮ 
РЇЮ [1] Save (as a global) the names of all the globals passed here for later use.
  GLOBALSРєљ РјЋSE.РѕєFРЇЎShare.globals.РјЋNL ┬»2 ┬»9  
РЇЮ [2] Merge the globals into this ns.
  РјЋTHIS РјЋNS РјЋSE.РѕєFРЇЎShare.globals
РЇЮ Set char. rendering of РјЋTHIS, so we can set РјЋTHIS.РјЋDF to something arbitrary.
  РѕєTHISРєљ РЇЋРјЋTHIS                

   :Section   РѕєF SOURCE
РЇЮ =======================================================================
РЇЮ РѕєF Utility 
РЇЮ =======================================================================
РЇЮ РѕєF: 
РЇЮ    resultРєљ {optsРєљРЇг|()} РѕЄ f-string [args]
РЇЮ See notes elsewhere on РѕєF itself.
РЇЮ 
  РѕЄ resultРєљ {opts} РѕєF args  
      :TRAP TRAP_ERRORS/0                                       
      РЇЮ Phase I: Set options and normalise args! 
      РЇЮ          User option styles? kw=keyword-style, pos'l=positional-style        
        :If  900РїХ0                                            РЇЮ No opts
            optsРєљ РјЋNS OPTS_DEFns                              РЇЮ Рєњ Make private copy of OPTS_DEFns                 
        :ElseIf 9=РјЋNC 'opts'                                  РЇЮ opts references a namespace
            optsРєљ РјЋNS OPTS_DEFns opts                         РЇЮ Рєњ Copy OPTS_DEFns and kw user opts                        
        :ElseIf 11 83РѕіРЇе РјЋDR opts РІё :AndIf OPTS_KW РЅЦРЇЦРЅб opts    РЇЮ Ints / booleans, none trailing
            optsРєљ OPTS_DEFns РјЋNSРЇЏРјЋVSET (OPTS_KWРєЉРЇеРЅбopts) opts  РЇЮ Рєњ Copy OPTS_DEFns and pos'l user opts
        :Else                                                 РЇЮ Kitchen sink 
            resultРєљ args Special opts РІё :Return               РЇЮ Рєњ Help / other special or error
        :EndIf 
        argsРєљ ,Рієargs  
      РЇЮ Phase II: Execute!  **************                   
      РЇЮ Determine output mode based on opts.dfn and execute.
        :Select opts.dfn  
      РЇЮ  0: Execute F-string    
        :Case  0              РЇЮ Executed code string refs args (as РЇх), not just РіЃРЇх.
            resultРєљ opts ((РіЃРјЋRSI){ РЇ║РЇ║РЇј РЇ║ ScanFStr РіЃРЇхРіБ РјЋEX 'opts' 'args'}) args 
      РЇЮ  1: Generate dfn code 
        :Case  1       
            resultРєљ (РіЃРјЋRSI) РЇј opts ScanFStr РіЃargs
      РЇЮ  ┬»1: Generate source code for dfn
        :Case ┬»1                                    
            resultРєљ opts ScanFStr РіЃargs  
      РЇЮ  Else: Run help or other special code           
        :Else          РЇЮ 'help', etc. => Give help, etc.      
            resultРєљ Special opts  
        :EndSelect   
    :Else 
        РјЋSIGNAL РіѓРјЋDMX.('EM' 'EN' 'Message' ,РЇЦРіѓ┬е('РѕєF ',EM) EN Message) 
    :EndTrap 
  РЇЮ! (C) Copyright 2025, 2026 Sam the Cat Foundation
  РѕЄ
   :EndSection   РѕєF Utility 
РЇЮ END ====================   РѕєF (User Function)   ==============================  

   :Section ScanFStr ( Top-Level РѕєF Service)
РЇЮ ============================   ScanFStr ( top-level routine )   ============================= РЇЮ
РЇЮ ScanFStr: 
РЇЮ    resultРєљ [options|РЇг] РѕЄ f_string
РЇЮ "Main" function called by РѕєF above. See the Executive section below.
РЇЮ Calls Major Field Recursive Scanners: 
РЇЮ Рѕў ScanAll:  text fields and space fields; 
РЇЮ Рѕў ScanCF:   code fields; 
РЇЮ Рѕў CFQS:     (code field) quoted strings
  ScanFStrРєљ {  

  РЇЮ ScanAll: Initiates scan of the f-string, checking for all fields.
  РЇЮ    Starts with a Text Field Scan.
  РЇЮ    If it sees an unescaped "{",
  РЇЮ       determines if Space Field (done internally) or Code Field (ScanCF).
  РЇЮ    Otherwise,
  РЇЮ       processes text field escapes and literals (if any).
  РЇЮ    ''Рєљ  accum РѕЄ str
  РЇЮ ├╗sr: R/W objects for this РѕєF ("user") call:
  РЇЮ   ├╗sr.cfBeg: start of field; 
  РЇЮ   ├╗sr.brC:   bracket count; 
  РЇЮ   ├╗sr.cfL:   length of code field string.
  РЇЮ   ├╗sr.flds:  the data fields.
  РЇЮ If it sees a non-escaped '{', it checks to see if it's followed by a Space Field: /\s*\}/.
  РЇЮ If not, it calls ScanCF to handle Code fields.
  РЇЮ Returns (via TFProc) the "final" array of fields (processed and formatted)
    ScanAllРєљ {  
        pРєљ TFBrk РЇх                                     РЇЮ (esc or lb) only. 
      p= РЅбРЇх: ├╗sr TFProc РЇ║, РЇх                           РЇЮ Nothing special. Process literals => return.
        pfxРєљ pРєЉРЇх РІё cРєљ pРїиРЇх РІё wРєљ (p+1)РєЊРЇх                 РЇЮ Found something!
      c= esc: (РЇ║, pfx, ├╗sr.nl TFEsc w) РѕЄ 1РєЊ w          РЇЮ char is esc. Process. => Continue
  РЇЮ   c= lb: We may have a SF or a CF. We complete this TF, then check SF vs CF.
  РЇЮ          If we have a SF, complete it here; Else, we recurse to Code Field processing
        _Рєљ ├╗sr TFProc РЇ║, pfx                           РЇЮ Update this text field and then...
        ├╗sr.cfBegРєљ w                                   РЇЮ Mark possible CF start (see SDCF in ScanCF)
      rb= РіЃw: '' РѕЄ 1РєЊ w                                РЇЮ SF 1. Null SF? Do nothing => Continue
        nSpРєљ wРєЊРЇеРєљ +/РѕД\' '= w                           РЇЮ Non-null SF?                         
      rb= РіЃw: '' РѕЄ 1РєЊ w РіБ ├╗sr.flds,Рєљ РіѓSFCode nSp       РЇЮ SF 2. Yes. Proc SF => Continue
        a wРєљ '' ScanCF w РіБ  ├╗sr.(cfL brC)Рєљ nSp 1       РЇЮ No. Get CF.
        ├╗sr.flds,Рєљ Ріѓlp, a, rp                          РЇЮ     Process CF.
        '' РѕЄ w                                         РЇЮ Continue scan.
    } РЇЮ End Text Field Scan 
  
  РЇЮ ScanCF - Scans a Code Field  
  РЇЮ      outStr remStr Рєљ accum РѕЄ str
  РЇЮ Modifies ├╗sr.cfL, ├╗sr.brC; calls CFQS and CFOm; modifies ├╗sr.omC and ├╗sr.cfL.  
  РЇЮ Returns the output from the code field plus more string to scan (if any)
  РЇЮ ScanCF will delete runs of leading and trailing blanks from output code; internal runs will remain.
    ScanCFРєљ {     
        ├╗sr.cfL+Рєљ 1+ pРєљ CFBrk РЇх                        РЇЮ ├╗sr.cfL is set in ScanAll above.  1: '{'
      p= РЅбРЇх:  РјЋSIGNAL ├фBr                              РЇЮ Missing "}" => Error. 
        pfxРєљ РЇ║, pРєЉРЇх 
        cРєљ   pРїиРЇх              
        wРєљ   (p+1)РєЊРЇх 
     (c= rb)РѕД ├╗sr.brCРЅц 1: (CFDfn pfx) w                РЇЮ Closing brace? Opt'lly Trim (CFDTrimR pfx) ==> and RETURN!!!
      cРѕі lb_rb: (pfx, c) РѕЄ wРіБ ├╗sr.brC+Рєљ -/c= lb_rb     РЇЮ Inc/dec ├╗sr.brC as appropriate
      cРѕі qtsL:  (pfx, a) РѕЄ wРіБ a wРєљ ├╗sr CFQS c w        РЇЮ Process quoted string.
      c= dol:   (pfx, scF) РѕЄ w                         РЇЮ $ => РјЋFMT 
      c= esc:   (pfx, a) РѕЄ wРіБ a wРєљ ├╗sr CFEsc w         РЇЮ `РЇх, `РІё, `A, `B, etc.
      c= omUs:  (pfx, a) РѕЄ wРіБ a wРєљ ├╗sr CFOm w          РЇЮ РЇ╣, alias to `РЇх (see CFEsc).
      c= libra: (pfx, ├╗sr libUtils.LibAuto w) РѕЄ w      РЇЮ ┬Б library.
    РЇЮ FUTURES: РЇЦ Adam B's CircleDiaeresis (optional).    
    РЇЮ          Рђд Adam B's Ellipsis (optional)    РіЄ Select / Sane Indexing.
      cРѕі FUTURES: w РѕЄРЇе pfx, scCD scEl scSel cРіЃРЇе cd el rsuРЇ│ c    
      ~cРѕіselfDoc: РјЋSIGNAL ├фCfLogic                     РЇЮ If guard true, CFBrk leaked unknown char.
    РЇЮ 'Рєњ', 'РєЊ' or '%'. See if a "regular" char/shortcut or self-defining code field      
      ├╗sr.brC>1: w РѕЄРЇе pfx, c scAРіЃРЇе c= pct              РЇЮ internal dfn => not SDCF
        pРєљ +/РѕД\' '=w
      rbРЅа РіЃpРєЊw:  w РѕЄРЇе pfx, c scAРіЃРЇе c= pct              РЇЮ not CF-final '}' => not SDCF
    РЇЮ SDCF: SELF-DEFINING CODE FIELD-- 
        cfLitРєљ AplQt ├╗sr.cfBegРєЉРЇе ├╗sr.cfL+ p            РЇЮ Put CF-literal in quotes
        fmtrРєљ scA scMРіЃРЇе c='Рєњ'                          РЇЮ vert (РєЊ or %) or horiz. (Рєњ) SDCF?
        (cfLit, fmtr, CFDfn pfx) (wРєЊРЇе p+1)             РЇЮ ==> RETURN!
    }   

РЇЮ ===========================================================================
РЇЮ Main: ScanFStr Executive 
РЇЮ ===========================================================================
РЇЮ ScanFStr executive begins here
РЇЮ    On entry: 
РЇЮ        РЇ║ is a namespace; 
РЇЮ        РЇх is the f-string, a possibly null char vector
РЇЮ    Returns either a matrix:   ├╗sr.dfn=0
РЇЮ    or a char. string:         ├╗sr.dfnРѕі 1 ┬»1
РЇЮ =========================================================================== 
РЇЮ Special namespaces used internally:
РЇЮ CALL-level (i.e. local to each РѕєF call)
РЇЮ    ├╗sr -    the "user" options passed in РѕєF's left argument, as well as 
РЇЮ             variables defined here (tracking internal scan state, etc.).
РЇЮ SESSION-level namespaces (shared across calls)
РЇЮ    p├бrms -  the default parameters internally or from file ./.РѕєF.
РЇЮ    ├╗Lib -  contains variables stored in РјЋTHIS.userLibrary.
РЇЮ
РЇЮ РєЊ┬»┬»┬»┬»┬»┬»┬»┬»┬»┬»┬»┬»┬»┬»┬»┬»┬»┬»┬»┬»┬»┬»┬»┬»┬»┬» 
РЇЮ РєЊ ├╗sr namespace variables.
РЇЮ РєЊ      Those marked U are User-specified Options on the РѕєF command line.
РЇЮ РєЊ      All the names below are defined in ├╗sr.
РЇЮ РєЊ Name    Init  Descr
РЇЮ ┬» ┬»┬»┬»┬»┬»┬»┬» ┬»┬»┬»┬»  ┬»┬»┬»┬»┬»┬»┬»┬»┬»┬»┬»┬»┬»┬»┬»┬»┬»┬»┬»┬»┬»┬»┬»┬»┬»┬»┬»┬»┬»┬»┬»┬»┬»┬»┬»┬»┬»┬»┬»┬»┬»┬»┬»┬»┬»┬»┬»┬»┬»┬»┬»┬»┬»┬»┬»┬»┬»┬»┬»┬» 
РЇЮ U dfn       0   Defines output format:
РЇЮ                 0 (return РѕєF mx output), 1 (return dfn), ┬»1 (return dfn code string)   
РЇЮ U verbose   0*  runtime verbosity/debug flag. 
РЇЮ             1*  1 if VERBOSE_RUNTIME global is 1.
РЇЮ U box       0   Display a box around each field, if set.
РЇЮ U auto      1   If 1, honors default/.РѕєF setting of p├бrms.autoРѕі 0 1.
РЇЮ U inline    0   If 0, puts ref to FString function.
РЇЮ             1*  If 1, puts shortcut code defs right in output string; 
РЇЮ                 1 if INLINE_DEF is set to 1.
РЇЮ U cache     1   Is the code cached for a specific command-line fstring and options?  
РЇЮ             0*  0 for all users, if FS_CACHE_ENABLED global is set to 0.
РЇЮ   l├«bObjs   РЇг   library autoload cache character vector of vectors (CVV)
РЇЮ   nl        CR  newline: nl (CR) or nlVis (the visible newline 'Рљц').  
РЇЮ   fields    РЇг   global field list (CVV)
РЇЮ   omC       0   omega index counter: current index for omega shortcuts (`РЇх, РЇ╣).
РЇЮ                 Local to the current РѕєF instance.
РЇЮ   brC       -   running count of braces '{' lb, '}' rb. Set in dfn ScanAll.
РЇЮ   cfL       -   code field running length (for SDCFs). Set in dfn ScanAll.
    ├╗srРєљ РЇ║                                
  РЇЮ Validate all options passed in ├╗sr (РЇ║).  dfnРѕі ┬»1 0 1; others Рѕі 0 1.
    coreРєљ |├╗sr.( dfn verbose box auto inline )         РЇЮ For cache, see FSCGet.
  11РЅа РјЋDR core: РјЋSIGNAL ├фOpt                           РЇЮ Are core opts bool?
    VMsgРєљ (РјЋРѕўРєљ)РЇБ(├╗sr.(verboseРѕД┬»1РЅаdfn))                 РЇЮ Verbose option message (returns РЇх) 
    key codeРєљ ├╗sr.cache FSCGet РЇх core                   РЇЮ Have we cached code ...  
  РЇгРЅб code: VMsg code                                   РЇЮ ... for this arg & core opts? 
РЇЮ   Shortcuts used explicitly (not just via esc+alphabetic): 
РЇЮ   See РЇЎLoad_Shortcuts 
    scA scCD scEl sc├љ scF scM scSelРєљ ├╗sr.inlineРіЃ┬е scA2  scCD2  scEl2  sc├љ2  scF2  scM2  scSel2
    ├╗sr.l├«bObjsРєљ РЇг                                   РЇЮ ┬Бibrary shortcut "autoload" cache...
    ├╗sr.nlРєљ ├╗sr.verboseРіЃ nl nlVis                      РЇЮ A newline escape (`РІё) maps onto nlVis if verbose mode.
    ├╗sr.fldsРєљ РЇг                                        РЇЮ output fields, each a CV (Char Vec)
    ├╗sr.omCРєљ  0                                        РЇЮ initialise omega counter to 0 (see `РЇх)
    ├╗sr.autoРѕДРєљ libUtils.p├бrms.auto                     РЇЮ auto can usefully be 1 only if p├бrms.auto is 1.     
РЇЮ   *** START THE SCAN ***                             РЇЮ РєЉРєЉРєЉРєЉРєЉРєЉРєЉРєЉРєЉРєЉРєЉРєЉРєЉРєЉРєЉРєЉРєЉРєЉРєЉРєЉРєЉРєЉ            
    fldsРєљ '' ScanAllРіб fstrРєљ РѕіРЇх                         РЇЮ    fstr: char vec of vecs => char vec                     
РЇЮ   *** SCAN COMPLETE ***                              РЇЮ РєЊРєЊРєЊРєЊРєЊРєЊРєЊРєЊРєЊРєЊРєЊРєЊРєЊРєЊРєЊРєЊРєЊРєЊРєЊРєЊРєЊРєЊ
  0= РЅбflds: VMsg '(1 0РЇ┤РЇг)', 'РЇе'/РЇе ├╗sr.dfnРЅа0            РЇЮ If there are no flds, return 1 by 0 matrix
    codeРєљ CFDfn (├╗sr.boxРіЃ scM sc├љ), OrderFlds flds     РЇЮ Order fields R-to-L so they will be evaluated L-to-R in РѕєF.           
  0=├╗sr.dfn: VMsg key FSCSet code                       РЇЮ Emit code ready to execute
    fstrQРєљ ',РЇеРіѓ', AplQt fstr                           РЇЮ Is ├╗sr.dfn (1,┬»1): add quoted fmt string (`РЇх0)
    VMsg key FSCSet lb, code, fstrQ, rb                 РЇЮ Emit ├╗sr.dfn-based str ready to cvt to ├╗sr.dfn in caller
  } РЇЮ ScanFStr 
РЇЮ === End of ScanFStr ========================================================  

   :EndSection ScanFStr ( Top-Level РѕєF Service)

   :Section Constants
РЇЮ ===========================================================================  
РЇЮ Constants (Generated at LOAD time)
РЇЮ ===========================================================================  
РЇЮ Simple char constants
  omРєљ 'РЇх'                                              РЇЮ РЇх not in cfBrklist, since it is not special. (See `РЇх).
  nl nlVisРєљ РјЋUCS 13 9252                               РЇЮ We use 13 (CR) for nl; 9252 (Рљц) for nlVis.
РЇЮ esc: Set value( always scalar) at LOAD time.
РЇЮ If global ESCAPE_CHAR is not present or is null, '`' is used.
  escРєљ '`' { 0=РјЋNC РЇх: РЇ║ РІё 0=РЅбeРєљРјЋOR РЇх: РЇ║ РІё РЇгРЇ┤e } 'ESCAPE_CHAR' 
РЇЮ Basic quote chars
  dq sqРєљ '"'''
РЇЮ qtsL qtsR:
РЇЮ    Generate left and right quote pairs... Double-quote first for efficiency.
РЇЮ    See QUOTES_SUPPLEMENTAL
  qtsL qtsRРєљ (dq,┬е2РЇ┤sq) { 0=РјЋNC РЇх: РЇ║ РІё 0=РЅбvРєљ РјЋOR РЇх: РЇ║ РІё РЇ║,┬е РєЊРЇЅРєЉ,Рієv } 'QUOTES_SUPPLEMENTAL'
РЇЮ Other basic characters
РЇЮ ' '{  }  (  )  $   РЇ╣    Рєњ  РєЊ  %   ┬Б     РЇЦ  Рђд  РіЄ
  sp lb rb lp rp dol omUs ra da pct libra cd el rsuРєљ ' {}()$РЇ╣РєњРєЊ%┬БРЇЦРђдРіЄ'  РЇЮ rsu: right shoe underbar
РЇЮ Seq. `РІё and `РЌЄ (see dia2[0, 1]) map onto РјЋUCS 13.
РЇЮ dia2[0]: Dyalog stmt separator (РІё) 
РЇЮ dia2[1]: Alternative character (РЌЄ) that is easier to read in some web browsers. 
  dia2Рєљ РјЋUCS 8900 9671           РЇЮ 'РІёРЌЄ' <-- hope that clears things up ;-) 
РЇЮ Order "break" chars roughly by frequency, high to low. 
РЇЮ We take dq to be high freq, but other quotes as low.
РЇЮ               "  `   {  }  $   РЇ╣    Рєњ  РєЊ  %   ┬Б      '┬Ф (default)
  cfBrkListРєљ  Рѕф dq esc lb rb dol omUs ra da pct libra, qtsL  
РЇЮ See defs of FUTURES, cd (РЇЦ), el (Рђд) rsu (РіЄ) 
  cfBrkList,Рєљ cd rsu el/РЇе cd rsu el Рѕі FUTURES
  tfBrkListРєљ esc lb                 
  lb_rbРєљ lb rb РІё om_omUsРєљ om omUs РІё sp_sqРєљ sp sq РІё   esc_lb_rbРєљ esc lb rb  
РЇЮ self-doc code field chars РєњРєЊ% (only on rhs of cf, ignoring blanks)
  selfDocРєљ ra da pct                                    

РЇЮ Error constants and fns  
    ├іРєљ { РЇ║Рєљ11 РІё Ріѓ'EN' РЇ║,РЇЦРіѓ 'Message' РЇх }
  ├фBrРєљ         ├і 'Unpaired brace "{"'
  ├фQtРєљ         ├і 'Unpaired quote in code field' 
  ├фCfLogicРєљ    ├і 'A logic error has occurred processing a code field'
  ├фOptРєљ        ├і 'Invalid option(s) in left argument. For help: РѕєFРЇе''help'''
  ├фScBadРєљ      ├і {'Sequence "`',РЇх,'" does not represent a valid shortcut.'}
               T1Рєљ{
                  t1Рєљ 'Sequence "`',РЇх,'" not valid in code fields outside strings.'
                  t2Рєљ 'Did you mean "',РЇх,'"?'
                  t1,nl,(17РЇ┤''),t2 
               }
  ├фEscРєљ        ├і T1 РІё РјЋEX 'T1'  
               t1Рєљ 'Help file "',HELP_HTML_FI,'" not found in current directory (CD)'
               t2Рєљ 'CD: "','"',РЇеРіЃ1 РјЋNPARTS ''
  ├фHelpFiРєљ  22 ├і t1,(РјЋUCS 13),(17РЇ┤''),t2 
               РјЋEX 't1' 't2'
   :EndSection Constants

   :Section F-String Cache (No Side Effects except on fscCache defined here.) 
   РѕЄ {isTrue}Рєљ FSCInitialise isTrue 
    :IF isTrue
      РЇЮ             kk: key list; cc: code-string list;
      РЇЮ             max: max # of keys to maintain; keep: min to maintain as kk fills.
        fscCacheРєљ ( kk: РЇг РІё cc: РЇг РІё max: FS_CACHE_MAX РІё keep: FS_CACHE_KEEP ) 
      РЇЮ FSCGet:   (keyРђ▓ code)Рєљ ├╗sr.cache РѕЄ keyРєљ (arg core)  
      РЇЮ    keyРђ▓ returned may be the <key> passed in OR РЇг.   
      РЇЮ If РЇ║РЅа0
      РЇЮ    - For key <key>, see if we have cached <code>, the fstr code equiv of the key.
      РЇЮ         If so, we are done: return <key code>. 
      РЇЮ         If not, return <key РЇг>, i.e. we should do a FSCSet after processing the f-string. 
      РЇЮ Else
      РЇЮ    - Return РЇг РЇг, i.e. set keyРђ▓Рєљ РЇг (no key) and code to 0.
        FSCGetРєљ fscCache. { 0= РЇ║: РЇг РЇг РІё pРєљkkРЇ│ РіѓРЇх РІё p= РЅбkk: РЇх РЇг РІё РЇх (pРіЃ cc) }  
      РЇЮ FSCSet: codeРєљ key РѕЄ code
      РЇЮ Add the k v pair to the arg cache, but keep a finite amount of
      РЇЮ the most recent entries. Return code.
      РЇЮ If key is РЇг, immediately return code.
        FSCSetРєљ fscCache. { 
          РЇгРЅАРЇ║: РЇх РІё (kk cc),Рєљ Ріѓ┬еРЇ║ РЇх                     РЇЮ Append РЇ║, РЇх to kk, cc.
          maxРЅЦ РЅбkk: РЇхРіБ kkРѕўРєљ 1500РїХ kk                   РЇЮ Hash keys <kk>
           РЇхРіБ kkРѕўРєљ 1500РїХ kkРєЉРЇе -keep                    РЇЮ Too many keys? Trunc and rehash.
        }  
    :Else РЇЮ F-String Caching Disabled
        FSCGetРєљ (РЇг РЇг)РЇе                                  РЇЮ Return constant (key and code value null)
        FSCSetРєљ Ріб                                       РЇЮ Return right arg, code.
    :EndIF 
   РѕЄ
   FSCInitialise FS_CACHE_ENABLED=1 
   :EndSection Argument Cache (No Side Effects) 

   :Section Utilities (Must Have Zero Side Effects) 
РЇЮ ===================================================================================
РЇЮ Utilities (fns/ops) for ScanFStr above.
РЇЮ Рѕў These must have zero side effects, except those reflected in ├╗sr-namespace objects.
РЇЮ ===================================================================================
РЇЮ See also CFSBrk.  
  TFBrkРєљ Рїі/РЇ│РѕўtfBrkList
  CFBrkРєљ Рїі/РЇ│РѕўcfBrkList
РЇЮ 
  TrimRРєљ РібРєЊРЇе-Рѕў(РіЦРЇеsp=Ріб)                                 РЇЮ Trim spaces on right...            
РЇЮ SFCode: Generate a SF code string; РЇх is a pos. integer. (Used in ScanAll above)
  SFCodeРєљ ('(',Ріб Ріб,Рѕў'РЇ┤'''')')РЇЋ 
РЇЮ (CFDfn 'xxx') => '{xxx}РЇх'                            РЇЮ Create literal code field dfn call
  CFDfnРєљ lbРѕў, ,Рѕў(rb,om)        

РЇЮ AplQt:  Created an APL-style single-quoted string.
  AplQtРєљ  sqРѕў(РіБ,РіБ,РЇеРібРібРЇц/РЇе1+=)   

РЇЮ TFEsc: esc_seqРєљ nl РѕЄ fstr 
РЇЮ    nl: current newline char;  fstr: starts with the char after the escape
РЇЮ Returns: the escape sequence.                        РЇЮ *** No side effects ***
  TFEscРєљ { 0= РЅбРЇх: esc РІё cРєљ 0РїиРЇх РІё cРѕі dia2: РЇ║ РІё cРѕі esc_lb_rb: c РІё esc, c } 

РЇЮ TFProc:  flds@CVVРєљ ├╗sr РѕЄ str
РЇЮ If a text field <str> is not 0-length, place in quotes and add it to ├╗sr.flds.
РЇЮ Ensure adjacent fields are sep by РЅЦ1 blank.
РЇЮ Returns the current array of fields (CVV)
  TFProcРєљ {0=РЅбРЇх: РЇ║.flds РІё РЇ║.flds,Рєљ Ріѓsp_sq, sq,РЇе РЇх/РЇе 1+ sq= РЇх РІё РЇ║.flds }  

РЇЮ CFEsc:  (code w)Рєљ ├╗sr РѕЄ fstr
РЇЮ Handle escapes  in Code Fields OUTSIDE of CF-Quotes.  
РЇЮ Returns code, the executable code, and w, the text of РЇх remaining.                                 
  CFEscРєљ {                                    
    0= РЅбРЇх: esc 
      c wРєљ (0РїиРЇх) (1РєЊРЇх) РІё РЇ║.cfL+Рєљ 1   
    cРѕі om_omUs: РЇ║ CFOm w                               РЇЮ Permissively allows `РЇ╣ as equiv to `РЇх OR РЇ╣ 
    c='L': (РЇ║ libUtils.LibAuto w) w                    РЇЮ Library shortcut: special (niladic) case
      pРєљ sc.Map c                                      РЇЮ Look for other shortcuts
    sc.nEsc> p: (РЇ║.inline pРіЃ sc.tbl) w                 РЇЮ Found? return code string.
    cРѕіРЇЦРјЋC РјЋA: РјЋSIGNAL ├фScBad c                         РЇЮ Nope: Unknown shortcut!
      РјЋSIGNAL ├фEsc c                                   РЇЮ Nope: An escape foll. by non-alphabetic.
  } РЇЮ End CFEsc 

 РЇЮ CFQS: CF Quoted String scan
  РЇЮ        qS wРєљ  ├╗sr РѕЄ qtL fstr 
  РЇЮ Рѕў qtL is the specific left-hand quote we saw in the caller.
  РЇЮ   We determine qtR internally.
  РЇЮ Рѕў fstr is the current format string, w/ the qtL removed, but end not determined..
  РЇЮ Рѕў For quotes with different starting and ending chars, e.g. ┬Ф ┬╗ (РјЋUCS 171 187).
  РЇЮ   If ┬Ф is the left qt, then the right qt ┬╗ can be doubled in the APL style, 
  РЇЮ   and a non-doubled ┬╗ terminates as expected.
  РЇЮ Рѕў Updates ├╗sr.cfL with length of actual quote string.
  РЇЮ Returns: qS w
  РЇЮ    qS: the string at the start of РЇх; w: the rest of РЇх 
  CFQSРєљ { ├╗srРєљ РЇ║ РІё qtL wРєљ РЇх 
      qtRРєљ (qtsLРЇ│ qtL)Рїи qtsR               
      CFSBrkРєљ Рїі/РЇ│Рѕў(esc qtR)    
    РЇЮ Recursive CF Quoted-String Scan. 
    РЇЮ    accum tL Scan РЇх
    РЇЮ accum: accumulates the quoted string
    РЇЮ lW:    the total length of w scanned SO FAR
    РЇЮ Returns (quoted string, lW: total length of w scanned)
      ScanРєљ {   
          a lW РєљРЇ║       
        0= РЅбРЇх: РЇ║  
          pРєљ CFSBrk РЇх  
        p= РЅбРЇх: РјЋSIGNAL ├фQt 
          c c2Рєљ 2РєЉ pРєЊ РЇх 
      РЇЮ See CFQSEsc, below, for handling of escapes in CF quoted strings.
      РЇЮ <skip> is how many characters were consumed...
        c= esc: (a, (pРєЉ РЇх), map) lW РѕЄ РЇхРєЊРЇе lW+Рєљ p+ skipРіБ map skipРєљ ├╗sr.nl CFQSEsc c2 qtR             
      РЇЮ Closing Quote: 
      РЇЮ c= qtR:  
      РЇЮ   Рѕў Now see if the NEXT char, c2, such that c2= qtR.
      РЇЮ     If so, it's a string-internal qtR. Only qtR need be doubled (i.e. '┬╗┬╗' => '┬╗').
        c2= qtR:  (a, РЇхРєЉРЇе p+1) lW РѕЄ РЇхРєЊРЇе lW+Рєљ p+2       РЇЮ Use APL rules for doubled ', ", or ┬╗
          (AplQt a, pРєЉРЇх) (lW+ p)                       РЇЮ Done... Return
      }
      qS lWРєљ '' 1 Scan w          
      qS (wРєЊРЇе ├╗sr.cfL+Рєљ lW)                            РЇЮ w is returned sans CF quoted string 
  } РЇЮ End CF Quoted-String Scan

РЇЮ CFQSEsc:  (map len)Рєљ nl РѕЄ c2 qtR, where 
РЇЮ           nl is the current newline char;
РЇЮ           c2 is the char AFTER the escape char,
РЇЮ           qtR  is the current right quote char.
РЇЮ c2= qt: esc+qtR is NOT treated as special-- this is APL, not C or HTML or ...
РЇЮ Returns (map len), where
РЇЮ         map is whatever the escape seq or char maps onto (possibly itself), and
РЇЮ         len is 1 if it consumed just the escape, and 2 if it ALSO consumed c2.
РЇЮ Side effect: none.       РЇЮ pattern   =>  literal    consumes   notes
  CFQSEscРєљ { c2 qtRРєљ РЇх     РЇЮ                          (# chars)
    c2Рѕі dia2: РЇ║  2         РЇЮ esc РІё          newline       2   newline is here РјЋUCS 13 (cr)
    c2= qtR: esc 1         РЇЮ esc qtR        esc           1   caller handles qtR next cycle.
    c2= esc: c2  2         РЇЮ esc esc        esc           2   2 esc => 1 esc literal
       (esc, c2) 2         РЇЮ esc <any>      esc <any>     2   esc is a literal
  } 

РЇЮ CFOm:   (omCode w)Рєљ ├╗sr РѕЄ РЇх 
РЇЮ РЇх: /\d*/, i.e. optional digits starting right AFTER `РЇх or РЇ╣ symbols.
РЇЮ Updates ├╗sr.cfL, ├╗sr.omC to reflect the # of digits consumed and their value.  
РЇЮ Returns omCode w:
РЇЮ    omCode: the emitted code for selecting from the РѕєF right arg (РЇх);
РЇЮ    w:      РЇх, just past the matched omega expression digits.
РЇЮ IntOpt: See IntOpt, just below.
  CFOmРєљ { 
      oLen oVal wРєљ IntOpt РЇх
  ├ЌoLen: ('(РЇхРіЃРЇе',')',РЇе 'РјЋIO+', РЇЋРЇ║.omCРєљ oVal ) wРіБ РЇ║.cfL+Рєљ oLen 
         ('(РЇхРіЃРЇе',')',РЇе 'РјЋIO+', РЇЋРЇ║.omC       ) wРіБ РЇ║.omC+Рєљ 1
  }

РЇЮ IntOpt: Does РЇх start with a valid sequence of digits (a non-neg integer)? 
РЇЮ Returns oLen oVal w:
РЇЮ   oLen:  len of sequence of digits (pos integer) or 0, 
РЇЮ   oVal:  the integer value of the digits found or 0, 
РЇЮ   w:     РЇх after skipping the prefix of digits, if any.
РЇЮ If oLen is 0, then there were no adjacent digits, i.e. (b) is 0 and (c) is РЇх unchanged.
  IntOptРєљ { 
    widРєљ +/РѕД\ РЇхРѕіРјЋD 
    wid (РіЃРіЃРїйРјЋVFI widРєЉ РЇх) (widРєЊ РЇх) 
  }  

РЇЮ OrderFlds
РЇЮ Рѕў User flds are effectively executed field-by-field L-to-R AND displayed in L-to-R order.
РЇЮ The process... 
РЇЮ   Рѕў ensures we reverse the order of fields, NOT the chars inside each field! 
РЇЮ   Рѕў reverses the ┬еfield┬е order now,
РЇЮ      Рѕў  evaluates each field via APL РЇј R-to-L, as normal, then 
РЇЮ   Рѕў reverses the ┬еresult┬е at execution time 
РЇЮ ... achieves apparent L-to-R field-by-field evaluation (but R-to-L within each field).
  OrderFldsРєљ 'Рїй',(РѕіРѕўРїй,Рѕў'РЇг') 

   :EndSection Utilities (Zero Side Effects)

:EndSection CORE
